    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, it doesn't feel like a \"moment\" or just being overwhelmed. it feels like a fundamental truth. like, if i'm the only one perceiving, doesn't that make everything else just... a simulation or a hallucination? i keep thinking about how nothing exists unless i'm here to witness it. does philosophy actually have an answer for that, or is it all just people trying to feel better about being alone?",
